WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:37.443
Welcome to Grade 1 English, Unit 2: Family Time. In this unit, your child learns the words for family members (mum, dad, sister, brother, grandma, grandpa), some breakfast and fruit words, and how to count from 1 to 10. They talk about who is in their family and how families help and have fun together. The gentle idea is that families love and help each other. The goal is warm, confident talking in English — not perfect spelling. In this short lecture, preview the key ideas and prepare for the independent lesson.

2
00:00:37.523 --> 00:01:02.731
By the end of this unit, you will be able to name the people in a family (mother, father, sister, brother, grandma, grandpa, baby). you will also name some breakfast foods and fruits (pancakes, cereal, milk, mango, banana, grapes). you will also count from 1 to 10, and count backwards from 10 to 1. Keep these goals in mind as you work.

3
00:01:02.811 --> 00:01:17.822
Your vocabulary work begins with these words: mother, mum, father, dad, sister, brother. Listen to each pronunciation in the vocabulary lab, study its meaning in context, and use the word accurately in your own discussion and writing.

4
00:01:17.902 --> 00:01:31.689
The reading sequence includes Breakfast at Grandma's House and Talk about Family Time. Read actively. Identify each text's central ideas, notice viewpoint and reliability, and support every inference with relevant evidence from the text.

5
00:01:31.769 --> 00:01:48.412
The first language focus is Language pattern 1. Listen to the model, point to the matching picture, then say the pattern: This is my ___. Notice the structure in the model examples, then apply it deliberately in connected sentences and paragraphs.

6
00:01:48.492 --> 00:02:03.911
In speaking, you will complete Speaking 1 - Listen and point. Organise your ideas, use evidence and respond clearly to questions. In writing, you will plan, draft, check and revise. Use the success criteria before submitting your work.

7
00:02:03.991 --> 00:02:20.633
You are ready to begin. Start with the vocabulary lab, continue through reading and comprehension, apply the grammar focus, and complete the speaking and writing practices. Use AI English for hints and feedback, and bring your questions to the live sessions.
